### VS Code REST Client Test File
### For testing accesses to another accounts

### 1. Register User A
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "userA@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Register User B
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "userB@test.com",
  "password": "password456"
}

### 3. Login User A (alternative to register if already exists)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "userA@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Login User B
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "userB@test.com",
  "password": "password456"
}

### 5. Get User A's profile (replace TOKEN_A with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A

### 6. User A accesses their own data by ID (should work ✅)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A

### 7. User A tries to access User B's data (should FAIL with 403 ✅)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/2
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A

### 8. User B accesses their own data (should work ✅)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/2
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_B

### 9. No authentication (should FAIL with 401 ✅)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1

### 10. Test protected endpoint
GET http://localhost:8080/api/auth/protected-test
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A
